Subject: Linux 2.2.13 ifconfig oddness "error fetching interface informati on: Device not found"
Sender: linux-kernel-owner@vger.kernel.org
Precedence: bulk
List-ID: <linux-kernel.vger.kernel.org>
X-Mailing-List: linux-kernel@vger.kernel.org
X-Lkml-Link: https://lkml.org/lkml/1999/11/6/43

On a multihomed Squid proxy server running RedHat 6.1 and linux 2.2.13 I get
this odd behaviour: ifconfig can't find any devices on the FIRST run. 
	# ifconfig
	: error fetching interface information: Device not found
Running ifconfig again works fine. It takes quite a while, several hours,
before ifconfig returns the same error again.
(This also happened with RedHat 6.0, which perhaps speaks against it being a
ifconfig problem.)
